# ============================================================
# .env — Project Secrets
# ============================================================
# SECURITY: Never commit this file. It's in .gitignore.
# Copy this to .env and fill in your real values.
# In production, use your cloud provider's env var management
# (Wrangler secrets for Workers, platform env vars elsewhere).
# ============================================================
#
# CONVENTION: Every secret this project uses must be listed
# here with an empty value. When you add a new secret to .env,
# add it here too — this is how other sessions and machines
# know what's needed. No real keys, not even expired ones.
#
# Example:
# DATABASE_URL=
# API_KEY=
# CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=
